Brazil May Tax Gasoline-Fueled Cars, Mercadante Tells Estado

-- B y   I u r i   D a n t a s
-- 
2011-04-11T13:17:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/brazil-may-tax-gasoline-fueled-cars-mercadante-tells-estado.html
The Brazilian government may levy
taxes on cars that use fuels other than ethanol in a bid to
stimulate use of the biofuel, O Estado de S.Paulo newspaper
 reported , citing an interview with Science and Technology
Minister Aloizio Mercadante.  The tax revenue would be used to create a fund to finance
research and development of ethanol, Mercadante said, according
to the Sao Paulo-based newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Iuri Dantas in Brasilia at 
 idantas@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  